      "raw_text": "signed to protect labor against being\ncheapened and degraded in the con-\nstructiOn of public works.\n\n\nContractors admit that they do not\nwant to hire Americans. They say\nthey can get more work out of men\nwho can not talk English. 1t is be-\nlever, however, that the real reason\nfor the embargo which has been plac-\ned upon American labor in the local\nfields is prompted by desire to get\nmen who are unfamiliar with the\nlaws and who will not raise a protest\nagainst long hours.\n\n\nThe law is clear. 1t states that no\ncontractor shall permit any employee\nto labor more than eight hours in any\none calendar day."
